text: I first stayed at Time Plaza way back in 2018 and became a fan instantly. Since then I have always chosen this hotel for my Dubai visits. It is one of those hotels that impress in a subtle manner with solid service, amenities and ambience. Service is a top feature here and I never had a reason to complain. Whether it's the front desk, room service, cleaning or at the restaurant, service is top notch. If I have to find a problem, it would be that the Check-in process can be faster. Food is quite good and the buffet's have excellent choice. The hotel has one of my favourite gyms with the right equipment and light traffic. One of the stand-out aspects about Time Grand is the quiet environment and consequent sleep quality. It's among the best I have seen in Dubai. Full marks here. I definitely recommend this hotel. However, if your business is towards the South then you might be looking at much longer travel times.

text: If you care about hygiene and kindness, this hotel is not the one for you. I booked it because it has good reviews and photos look quite good, but you should know certain things. 1. Room condition is quite dirty. Bathtub seems that it has not been properly cleaned for a long time. When I tried to take a shower, I saw hairs from the previous customer and dark water stains. Eventually, I had to change the room because I did not want to wash there. (I did not even take a photo because it was disgusting but I can prove it with the receipt of hotel.) 2. A female receptionist Rayna (not sure 100%of her name) was quite rude. She said I cannot borrow cutlery because I ordered from a restaurant outside the hotel. She said it's only allowed to use when I use their restaurant. I have never heard such thing in a hotel. A colleague next to her listened the whole conversation and brought me plastic cutlery. It was a bizarre experience. Overall conversation with her was quite unpleasant. Maybe she was upset because I requested her to change the room. Other staff Jessica was quite nice and communicated well. 3. Sauna and swimming facilities are not so clean either. 4. If you request something to be done, it takes longer time than other hotel services. I waited an hour for checking the bathtub condition from their staff. Other than that, it was OK, the bed and pillows are quite comfortable.

Passing through the plane, you must book a hotel within 28 hours. First look at the price and reviews, not bad. More than 200 surprised me.Great value for the following reasons:1. The location is good. The airport is about 7 kilometers away from the hotel. I took a taxi for 24 yuan, which is equivalent to 48 yuan.2. The hotel facilities are very complete. It must be five-star when it opened, and now it should meet the five-diamond standard in Ctrip. The room has everything you should have. Many compatriots commented on slippers and toothbrushes, which are actually misunderstandings. The hotel is participating in the creation of green hotel environmental protection activities. Just like in China, why don‚Äôt you bring your own? Of course, slippers and hair dryers can be delivered to the room by the hotel when needed, no problem.3. SPA, gym, and outdoor swimming pool are all highlights and worth experiencing. If you need a discount for the SPA, you can go to the front desk to find the manager.4. I didn't experience catering, but the restaurant is very beautiful, as are the bars and cafes.5. There are many Indian restaurants around, the most recommended one is 500 meters from the hotel, there is an Indian restaurant called FRAZER under the light rail viaduct, second * KFC McDonald's, the food is served quickly, and there are too many delicacies.6. The hotel staff are very friendly and professional. From porter to hotel manager. Special thanks to their service, Yam, Jessica, Udaai at the front desk, and room attendant, manager Ahmed.Tips:1. Dubai is safe, fashionable and convenient. Public transportation is basically paid for by China, and even the English-speaking boys in the subway are the ones in the Beijing subway. Recommend a one-day subway red card, which can only be bought in the morning, 22D. It can be used for various means of transportation, including boats.2. It is recommended to charter a car with the Ctrip travel steward for one day when the family travels. The service is good and the enjoyment is noble. Experience it yourself at other times, public transport should avoid the peak hours of 7.00 to 8.30 in the morning and 5.00 to 7.30 in the evening.

text: If I could give 10 stars, I would! Here's my story and review of why: On February 9th, my family embarked on a leisure trip to Dubai and we stayed at Time Grand Plaza Hotel. While in Dubai, and two days before heading back home, both my children tested positive for COVID. I had to get back to work urgently, so I left Dubai for back home, and my wife and children were still at the hotel. Evangeline and the hotel management team played a formidable role in balancing guest safety, adhering to hotel policy, while going above and beyond to accommodate my family. My wife and kids were confined to a hotel room due to law, and were advised by Dubai Health Authority that they can not leave the room until their quarantine period was over. Since I left my family alone and had to be back home, my family felt safe and at home because of the outstanding management at Time Grand Plaza Hotel. Because I was separated from my family, I was obviously very disturbed and concerned, and when I got back home, I also tested positive, so now I was in quarantine in a different country and my wife and kids were quarantined in Dubai at the hotel. Every single day, Evangeline personally followed up with me, asked how my family is doing, and showed a great amount of care and empathy. Her and her team went out of their way to treat my family as "guests" rather than clients. They felt welcomed, they felt "home," and they had an entire team who took their comfort as their highest priority. Not one time did my family feel uncomfortable or unwelcome, even though they were COVID-positive. The hotel, like others, had a policy for delivery drivers not being able to go upstairs and deliver food. Since my family was COVID-positive, they too were not allowed to come downstairs to collect food, since the government restrictions meant they must stay in their rooms. Despite this situation, the hotel found a creative solution, went out of their way, and had staff members collect food from delivery drivers several times daily and deliver upstairs personally to my family. This gesture is unheard of, and this is going way beyond the call of duty to accommodate a family and re-emphasize that they are in safe, caring hands. From a financial standpoint, the hotel gave the best possible rate, and never once did they mention the financials or that bills need to be paid or cleared. They did not "push" on this angle as they knew that this situation was unplanned, so money was not an issue. Evangeline and team considered my family as guests, as people, and they showed the human factor outweighs any financial factor. Only after my family checked out, did I receive a confirmation message that payment was cleared, and they never mentioned it during their stay, so as to keep us comfortable. To the team, the payment / financials were the least of concerns, as the team focused on keeping my family healthy and well - this was the priority and this shall not be forgotten. In closing, if Google allowed me to give 10 stars instead of 5, I would have. Evangeline and her management team went above and beyond to accommodate our very difficult situation - they had to be creative with adhering to policy, while playing a very fine balance between policy and the human factor, and they balanced both extremely well. The fact that they treated us as their most important guests rather than just "customers" makes me want to thank them over and over, and whenever I come to Dubai, I will be looking nowhere else - I will come straight to Time Grand Plaza because I know that I will be in safe hands, will deal with an empathetic management team, and a team that will do anything to keep their guests satisfied. Thank you Evangeline and team!

text: Great hotel close to the airport. Convenient location near the metro. The rooms are spacious. The staff is very friendly, tactful and polite. I express special gratitude to our accompanying Yunus.

I landed at midnight and wanted to find a budget hotel near the airport before moving to the dock area, however, this was 8km away so not as close as I initially thought but close enough. I only stayed one night and got an upgrade. The room was huge so no complaints there. Many nearby restaurants are open at night, but this hotel is not in the city center so you will end up paying a lot for a taxi as there are no metro options nearby. The breakfast buffet was great, with lots of local and international dishes. The hotel's leisure area was nice, unfortunately I didn't have time to see the pool or gym. Nice hotel with lovely staff.

Breakfast is a buffet. The food is quite varied. There were dishes of both Arabic and European cuisine. The rooms are in good condition. You can choose a smoking or non-smoking room. There was no hairdryer in the room, you need to ask at the reception. Outdoor pool. Overall the impressions are positive. It‚Äôs not far from the metro, about 10 minutes, but along the road and in the sun. It takes an hour and a half by metro to get to Dubai Mall, and even longer to get to the bay. If you don't need to go to the center, then the hotel is good. And it is located far from attractions.
